				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: PON Dogs<a name="66427"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 11 04 5:57 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Charm soloing the dogs is easy. Here is a safe way to do it without &quot;swarming&quot;:
<br />

<br />
- 1) there are 2 dogs away from the rest. Pull them first. Charm one, kill the other. Chant the survivor down.
<br />

<br />
- 2) Now lull all but 2 of the camp, then pull those 2 (should be only 6 in camp i think). Charm one, kill the other. Chant the survivor down.
<br />

<br />
- 3) Repeat 2 until camp cleared. After you break the camp once, just wait till 2 respawn then pull them.
<br />

<br />
Tips:
<br />

<br />
- you usually dont have to lull the entire camp, doggies far away from each other arent aggro linked.
<br />

<br />
- When charming and killing 2 dogs, usually charm breaks at least once. When it breaks, re-charm the one with lower health. When one dies you want your pet to have as low health as possible.
<br />

<br />
- If your pet looks like he is gonna die keep dispel up to break charm.
<br />

<br />
This method takes about 20-30 mins to clear the camp and I have never died doing it. One clearing yields about half a yellow at 55.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
